DocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527057\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eas1665702994900.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eas1665702994900.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eas1665702994900.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eas1665702994900\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Running Uniface Services on the iSeries\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To run a service, the Uniface Server must be able to find the UAR containing the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.svc</span> file and its signature.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"eas1665702994900__li_d29168e1_d29169e1_d29170e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"eas1665702994900__p_d66551e1_d66552e1_d66553e1\">Compile the service, its signature, and any\n               object it needs into an archive for use by the Uniface Server\n                  (<span class=\"ph filepath\">USERVER</span>). </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">To compile objects directly to the iSeries, set <code class=\"ph codeph\">$resources_output</code>\n                  in the client assignment file so that it points to an archive on your iSeries\n                  machine. </p>\n<p class=\"p\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eas1665702994900__pre_sln_sw1_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$AS4 = TCP:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Machinename</var>+13001|<var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>\n[SETTINGS]\n$resources_output = $AS4:my_svc.uar </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eas1665702994900__p_d66554e1_d66555e1_d66556e1\">Alternatively, you can transfer a UAR in\n                  binarymode to the iSeries.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"eas1665702994900__li_d29171e1_d29172e1_d29173e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"eas1665702994900__p_d66557e1_d66558e1_d66559e1\">In the client assignment file, redirect service\n               activation to the iSeries Uniface Router (<span class=\"ph filepath\">UROUTER</span>).</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$AS4 = TCP:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Machinename</var>+13001|<var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>\n  \n[SERVICES_EXEC]\nA* $AS4:A*</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\"> In this example, activation by the client of any service whose name starts with\n                  an ‘A’ will be routed to an ANY USERVER on the iSeries. For more information, see\n                     <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"svf1665702769463.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svf1665702769463.html\" title=\"Assignments in the sections [SERVICES_EXEC] and [REPORTS_EXEC] direct the execution of each service or report component to a Uniface Server specified in the [PATHS] section.\">Assignments for Remote Services and Reports</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527057\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527057\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Running Uniface Services on the iSeries Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Running Uniface Services on the iSeries To run a service, the Uniface Server must be able to find the UAR containing the .svc file and its signature. Compile the service, its signature, and any object it needs into an archive for use by the Uniface Server ( USERVER ). To compile objects directly to the iSeries, set $resources_output in the client assignment file so that it points to an archive on your iSeries machine. For example: [PATHS] $AS4 = TCP: Machinename +13001| User | Password [SETTINGS] $resources_output = $AS4:my_svc.uar Copy Alternatively, you can transfer a UAR in binarymode to the iSeries. In the client assignment file, redirect service activation to the iSeries Uniface Router ( UROUTER ). For example: [PATHS] $AS4 = TCP: Machinename +13001| User | Password [SERVICES_EXEC] A* $AS4:A* Copy In this example, activation by the client of any service whose name starts with an ‘A’ will be routed to an ANY USERVER on the iSeries. For more information, see Assignments for Remote Services and Reports . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}